&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an &lt;strong&gt;Associate Program Manager&lt;/strong&gt; with a strong engineering background to support and/or lead the execution of complex embedded systems programs for defense and space applications. This role is ideal for a hands-on technical program professional who can work closely with engineering teams, drive cross-functional execution, and help ensure programs meet cost, schedule, technical, contractual, compliance, and customer commitments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Depending on program scope, this individual may support a Program Manager on larger or more complex programs and/or take ownership of smaller programs, projects, or work packages with appropriate guidance. The role will help manage day-to-day program execution, track deliverables, identify risks, drive actions to closure, and support customer and leadership communications.&lt;br&gt;This role is well suited for someone who thrives in a fast-paced, resource-constrained environment and is comfortable operating with limited information,&amp;nbsp;solving problems proactively, and wearing multiple hats.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, the essential responsibilities are:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and/or lead the planning, execution, and delivery of embedded systems programs, projects, or work packages for defense and space customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Program Managers on larger programs and/or manage smaller scoped programs, projects, or work packages with appropriate oversight.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help manage program performance across cost, schedule, technical scope, risk, quality, contractual deliverables, and customer satisfaction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with engineering teams to understand technical&amp;nbsp;requirements, track progress, identify risks, and support tradeoff discussions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, maintain, and update integrated program plans, schedules, risk registers, action trackers, customer deliverable trackers, and status reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive cross-functional follow-up across engineering, manufacturing, supply chain, quality, contracts, finance, business development, and customer-facing teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify program risks, blockers, dependencies, and execution gaps;&amp;nbsp;support mitigation planning and drive assigned actions to closure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate effectively in ambiguous environments, helping the team make progress even when information is incomplete or priorities are evolving.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support recovery efforts for challenged programs by improving visibility, establishing clear action plan

