&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Configuration/Data Manager II performs configuration and data management activities under the general oversight of senior Configuration/Data Management personnel. This position is responsible for supporting and executing technical baseline management, engineering change control, and document management processes to ensure hardware, software, and technical data are accurately maintained, properly authorized, and fully traceable throughout the product life cycle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and control hardware, software, and documentation baselines to ensure configuration integrity, accuracy, traceability, and consistency throughout the product lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee configuration control activities, including creation, revision, review, and approval of engineering drawings, specifications, technical data packages (TDPs), and related documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer Engineering Change Requests (ECRs) and change workflows to ensure proper evaluation, approval, implementation, and tracking of configuration changes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create agendas, schedule, facilitate, and document Configuration Control Board (CCB) meetings and associated action items.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain CM databases, repositories, and records to ensure all configuration documentation remains current, accurate, and audit ready.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;With oversight from senior team members generate, analyze, and present configuration status accounting reports, change activity metrics, audit findings, and program data to leadership and quality teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support senior team members participating in Functional Configuration Audits (FCA), Physical Configuration Audits (PCA), and internal/external compliance assessments.&lt;/li&gt;
