&lt;p&gt;The position reports to the VP of Product Design and is part of the Engineering department based in San Diego, CA. This role is 100% onsite.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, the essential functions are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, develop and test FPGA designs for space communication systems, including but not limited to, resampling, filtering, mixing and error correction coding&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in architecting solutions against requirements and implementing those solutions in various FPGA technologies or platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize FPGA designs for speed, performance and resource utilization and conducting thorough testing and validation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the day-to-day operations of the engineering team and the development and execution of projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support internal and external design and development reviews with related documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in project resource allocations overseeing that engineers are efficiently allocated and have a balanced workload&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in proposals and trade studies, including evaluating contractor and subcontractor proposals for technical feasibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review contract/proposals/opportunities, with emphasis on SOW, technical requirements, data requirements and statement of compliance before acceptance and transfer it to the engineering team after acceptance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
