&lt;p&gt;The Machine Shop Lead / CNC Machining Mentor for the NASA HUNCH Program is responsible for serving as the lead machinist and student-facing mentor for NASA HUNCH in California, producing certified aerospace hardware while training high school teachers and students across partner schools to NASA manufacturing standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position reports to the HUNCH Director of Projects and is part of the NASA HUNCH Program based in Long Beach, CA. This role will be based in Long Beach, CA.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, the essential functions are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead production of aerospace-grade flight and non-flight hardware on schedule, on budget, and under full QA oversight.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review engineering drawings, GD&amp;amp;T, and specifications; assess manufacturability and flag risks early.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and approve manufacturing plans, work instructions, and process documentation capturing controls, traceability, and quality requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write and optimize CNC programs for multi-axis mills, lathes, and other machine tools; manage tooling, fixturing, and setup.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with AS9100, NASA, and applicable military standards across all machining operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assess partner-school readiness and deliver training that elevates students and teachers to NASA hardware standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expose students to the full manufacturing lifecycle — drawing review, programming, setup, machining, deburring, cleaning, and inspection.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion safety and quality culture across the home shop and every partner-school HUNCH facility, including FAI and nonconformance resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
